<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-ansi-language:IT'>Spiegazioni
dell'esercitazione del 5 Novembre 2004<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:IT'>Scopo dell’esercitazione</span></b><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:IT'>: scopo dell’esercitazione è di
prendere confidenza con i principali meccanismi di interazione ed animazione di
OpenGL e di GLUT attraverso la modifica e completamento di un semplice
programma che visualizza un cubo ed una sfera. <b>Nota bene: </b>Tutte le
operazioni di disegno e di modifica delle matrici devono (preferibilmente)
essere effettuate nella Display Function, chiamata <i>disegna</i> nel nostro
caso. Nelle altre funzioni, dovete soltanto cambiare i valori dei parametri che
vengono usati dalla Display Function.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:IT'>Cose da
fare:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>1)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Create nella vostra Home Directory (selezionabile dal desktop) una
directory per l’esercitazione<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>2)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Copiate in questa directory sul vostro computer il file cuboInterattivo.c e
Spiegazioni.doc (questo file)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>3)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Avviate Visual C++ ed aprite la vostra copia del file cuboInterattivo.c<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>4)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Compilate il file. Vi verrà chiesto di creare un default workspace.
Rispondete di si.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>5)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Se non ci sono errori, mandate in esecuzione il programma. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Aprite il codice e cercate di capirne il funzionamento.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span style='mso-ansi-language:
IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>7)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Aprite il
codice e cercate di capirne il funzionamento. Le funzioni gluPerspective e
gluLookAt sono descritte nei lucidi su OpenGL (30-31 la gluPerspective e 26 la
gluLoookAt). Maggiori dettagli nel file </span><span lang=EN-GB>glu1.3.pdf alle
pagine 11 e 12)</span><span style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>8)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Introducete le seguenti modifiche in ordine:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>a.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Provate a modificare la gluPerspective, e la
gluLookAt per vedere l’effetto.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>b.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Ruotate il cubo di 20 gradi anche rispetto
all’asse y<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>c.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Inserite una sfera di colore blu posizionata coon
il centro in (0, 3, 0). L’istruzione per il disegno della sfera è
glutSolidSphere(r, 10, 10) che disegna una sfera di raggio r con centro
nell’origine. Il secondo e terzo parametro definisco il numero di spicchi
orizzontali e verticali in cui è divisa la sfera, che in realtà è sfaccettata.
Scalate la sfera in modo che diventi un ellissoide con il raggio sull’asse y
maggiore di quello sugli assi x e z. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>d.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Modificare la gluPerspective, e la gluLookAt per
centrare la scena complessiva con l’ellissoide<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>e.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:IT'>Provate ad inserire istruzioni
nella DisplayFunc (disegna) e nella MouseFunc (topo) in modo da far ruotare la
scena intorno all’asse z ogni volta che viene premuto il tasto destro del
mouse.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:IT'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>f.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Aggiungere un’animazione che ruota tutta la scena intorno all’asse y usando
<st1:PersonName ProductID="la IdleFunc" w:st="on">la IdleFunc</st1:PersonName>
(animazione)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-ansi-language:
IT'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><b><span
lang=EN-GB style='mso-fareast-language:IT'>7.5 glutMouseFunc<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>glutMouseFunc </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>sets the mouse callback for
the <i>current window</i>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><b><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>Usage<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>void glutMouseFunc(void (*func)(int button,
int state, int x, int y));<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>func </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:
10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>The new mouse callback function.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><b><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>Description<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none'><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;
mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>glutMouseFunc </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>sets the mouse
callback for the <i>current window</i>. When a user presses and releases mouse buttons
in the window, each press and each release generates a mouse callback. The </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>button </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>parameter is one of </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT LEFT BUTTON</span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>, </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT MIDDLE BUTTON</span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>, or </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT RIGHT BUTTON</span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>. For systems with only two mouse
buttons, it may not be possible to generate </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT MIDDLE BUTTON </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>callback. For systems with a
single mouse button, it may be possible to generate only a </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT LEFT BUTTON </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>callback. The </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>state </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>parameter is either </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT UP </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>or </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT DOWN </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:
10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>indicatingwhether the callback was due to a
release or press respectively. The </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;mso-fareast-language:
IT'>x </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:
IT'>and </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;
mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>y </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>callback parameters
indicate the window relative coordinates when the mouse button state changed. If
a </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;
mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT DOWN </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:IT'>callback for a
specific button is triggered, the program can assume a </span><span lang=EN-GB
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;
mso-fareast-language:IT'>GLUT UP </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;
mso-fareast-language:IT'>callback for the same buttonwill be generated
(assuming the window still has a mouse callback registered) when the mouse button
is released even if the mouse has moved outside the window. If a menu is
attached to a button for a window, mouse callbacks will not be generated for
that button. During a mouse callback, </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:Courier;mso-fareast-language:
IT'>glutGetModifiers </span><span lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;
mso-fareast-language:IT'>may be called to determine the state of modifier keys when
the mouse event generating the callback occurred. Passing </span><span
lang=EN-GB style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Courier;mso-bidi-font-family:
